title: Kasehti
text:
Kasehti is a village in <a href="Rahi%2C%20Raebareli">Rahi</a> block of <a href="Rae%20Bareli%20district">Rae Bareli district</a>, <a href="Uttar%20Pradesh">Uttar Pradesh</a>, <a href="India">India</a>. It is located 8 km from <a href="Rae%20Bareli">Rae Bareli</a>, the district headquarters. As of 2011, it has a population of 1,400 people, in 271 households. It has one primary school and no healthcare facilities.
The <a href="1961%20Census%20of%20India">1961 census</a> recorded Kasehti as comprising 3 hamlets, with a total population of 516 people (267 male and 249 female), in 100 households and 95 physical houses. The area of the village was given as 571 <a href="acre">acre</a>s.
The <a href="1981%20Census%20of%20India">1981 census</a> recorded Kasehti as having a population of 709 people, in 130 households, and having an area of 232.70 <a href="hectare">hectare</a>s. The main staple foods were given as wheat and rice.
